    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>Integer i = theLong != null ? theLong.intValue() : null;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>or if you don't need to worry about null:</p>\n\n<pre><code>// auto-unboxing does not go from Long to int directly, so\nInteger i = (int) (long) theLong;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>And in both situations, you might run into overflows (because a Long can store a wider range than an Integer).</p>\n\n<p>Java 8 has a helper method that checks for overflow (you get an exception in that case):</p>\n\n<pre><code>Integer i = theLong == null ? null : Math.toIntExact(theLong);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
