    "question_id" : 5804043,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You'll need to type cast it.</p>\n\n<pre><code>long i = 100L;\nint k = (int) i;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Bear in mind that a long has a bigger range than an int so you might lose data.</p>\n\n<p>If you are talking about the boxed types, then read the <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/1.5.0/docs/api/java/lang/Long.html#intValue%28%29\">documentation</a>.</p>\n"
