      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@user64141 Type casting in Java is a complicated issue. Casting Objects is fine, because you are actually not changing anything, just looking at the same object in a different way. But in this case, you have a chain of meaningful casts, from Object to primitive and then, through the madness of autoboxing, to object again, even though the syntax suggests it&#39;s another primitive. To me, this is a misuse of both boxing and primitive conversion. Not everything that can be done should be done."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 138128,
