    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>In java ,there is a rigorous way to convert a long to int</p>\n\n<p>not only lnog can convert into int,any type of class extends Number can convert to other Number type in general,here I will show you how to convert a long to int,other type vice versa.</p>\n\n<pre><code>Long l = 1234567L;\nint i = org.springframework.util.NumberUtils.convertNumberToTargetClass(l, Integer.class);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 38455,
      "reputation" : 30460,
      "user_id" : 110358,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 90,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/13c7ad63eb27047a7ff869d27e40c1ad?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Jacob Marble",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/110358/jacob-marble"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 20,
    "last_activity_date" : 1516079938,
    "last_edit_date" : 1516079938,
    "creation_date" : 1366752432,
    "answer_id" : 16179476,
    "question_id" : 5804043,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you care to check for overflows and have <a href=\"https://code.google.com/p/guava-libraries/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Guava</a> handy, there is <a href=\"https://google.github.io/guava/releases/23.6-jre/api/docs/com/google/common/primitives/Ints.html#checkedCast%28long%29\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Ints.checkedCast()</code></a>:</p>\n\n<pre><code>int theInt = Ints.checkedCast(theLong);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://code.google.com/p/guava-libraries/source/browse/guava/src/com/google/common/primitives/Ints.java#86\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">The implementation</a> is dead simple, and throws <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/IllegalArgumentException.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">IllegalArgumentException</a> on overflow:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static int checkedCast(long value) {\n  int result = (int) value;\n  checkArgument(result == value, \"Out of range: %s\", value);\n  return result;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6076356,
      "reputation" : 2094,
      "user_id" : 4743608,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 40,
      "profile_image" : "https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-frpdff6ZlUM/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABY/Gw9468dQjLM/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Adi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4743608/adi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1436448640,
    "last_edit_date" : 1436448640,
    "creation_date" : 1436447209,
    "answer_id" : 31318428,
    "question_id" : 5804043,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>The best simple way of doing so is:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static int safeLongToInt( long longNumber ) \n    {\n        if ( longNumber &lt; Integer.MIN_VALUE || longNumber &gt; Integer.MAX_VALUE ) \n        {\n            throw new IllegalArgumentException( longNumber + \" cannot be cast to int without changing its value.\" );\n        }\n        return (int) longNumber;\n    }\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5180762,
      "reputation" : 409,
      "user_id" : 4146553,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-CtbFkr5YL_s/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAlk/ypzMI2KvKMQ/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Edwin Miguel",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4146553/edwin-miguel"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1472685390,
    "creation_date" : 1472685390,
    "answer_id" : 39260442,
    "question_id" : 5804043,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Assuming not null  longVal</p>\n\n<pre><code>Integer intVal = ((Number)longVal).intValue();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>It works for example y you get an Object that can be an Integer or a Long. I know that is ugly, but it happens...</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3125702,
      "reputation" : 625,
      "user_id" : 2644597,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 50,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3730e53c3e0a105846d261d12b37c62f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Dushyant Sapra",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2644597/dushyant-sapra"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 12,
    "last_activity_date" : 1487310125,
    "creation_date" : 1487310125,
    "answer_id" : 42290250,
    "question_id" : 5804043,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you are using Java 8 Do it as below</p>\n\n<pre><code>    import static java.lang.Math.toIntExact;\n\n    public class DateFormatSampleCode {\n        public static void main(String[] args) {\n            long longValue = 1223321L;\n            int longTointValue = toIntExact(longValue);\n            System.out.println(longTointValue);\n\n        }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11598306,
      "reputation" : 411,
      "user_id" : 8496330,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8de5ed444e2dd5cb1313a78ba8a2198e?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Bala",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/8496330/bala"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
