      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "why not we use the above statement as below :  Integer intVal = longVal != null ? Math.toIntExact(longVal) : null;  A usual practice"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 472248,
      "reputation" : 20384,
      "user_id" : 880619,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 100,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/z2G6A.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Jasper de Vries",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/880619/jasper-de-vries"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 10,
    "last_activity_date" : 1593771368,
    "last_edit_date" : 1593771368,
    "creation_date" : 1523028722,
    "answer_id" : 49696291,
    "question_id" : 5804043,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In Java 8 you can use <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/Math.html#toIntExact-long-\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>Math.toIntExact</code></a>. If you want to handle <code>null</code> values, use:</p>\n<pre><code>Integer intVal = longVal == null ? null : Math.toIntExact(longVal);\n</code></pre>\n<p>Good thing about this method is that it throws an <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/ArithmeticException.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>ArithmeticException</code></a> if the argument (<code>long</code>) overflows an <code>int</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 9958876,
      "reputation" : 3209,
      "user_id" : 7368826,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 25,
      "profile_image" : "https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-4ZbdUCL5TtY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAEs/7LgtAp-9ITg/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Anjal Saneen",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7368826/anjal-saneen"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1526181186,
    "creation_date" : 1526181186,
    "answer_id" : 50312434,
    "question_id" : 5804043,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Using toIntExact(long value) returns the value of the long argument, throwing an exception if the value overflows an int. it will work only API level 24 or above.</p>\n\n<pre><code>int id = Math.toIntExact(longId);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
